Rinse @rice{250%g} and soak it for ~{30%minutes}.
In a pot, heat @oil{30%ml} and add @onions{2}, sauté until golden brown.
Add @chicken{500%g} and cook until it turns white.
Stir in @yogurt{200%g}, @ginger{20%g}, and @garlic{20%g}.
Add @tomatoes{2}, @chili powder{10%g}, @turmeric{5%g}, @cumin{5%g}, and @coriander{5%g}. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.
In a separate pot, boil @water{500%ml} and add soaked rice. Cook until it's 70% done.
Layer the partially cooked rice over the chicken mixture.
Garnish with @saffron{1%g} dissolved in @milk{10%ml}.
Cover and simmer for ~{15%minutes}.

